.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-EXPORT 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.7.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-export \- Export dashboards to raw/, prompt/, and provisioning/ files.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard export [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Export dashboards to raw/, prompt/, and provisioning/ files.
.PP
Use this when you need a local export tree for later import, review, diff, or file\-provisioning workflows. The prompt/ lane is for Grafana UI import, not dashboard API import; use dashboard raw\-to\-prompt when you need to convert ordinary or raw dashboard JSON into prompt JSON.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-export\-dir
target directory for the export tree.
.TP
.B \-\-org\-id
export one explicit Grafana org.
.TP
.B \-\-all\-orgs
export each visible org into per\-org subdirectories. Prefer Basic auth.
.TP
.B \-\-flat
write files directly into each export variant directory.
.TP
.B \-\-overwrite
replace existing export files.
.TP
.B \-\-without\-dashboard\-raw, \-\-without\-dashboard\-prompt, \-\-without\-dashboard\-provisioning
skip a variant.
.TP
.B \-\-provisioning\-provider\-name, \-\-provisioning\-provider\-org\-id, \-\-provisioning\-provider\-path
customize the generated provisioning provider file.
.TP
.B \-\-provisioning\-provider\-disable\-deletion, \-\-provisioning\-provider\-allow\-ui\-updates, \-\-provisioning\-provider\-update\-interval\-seconds
tune provisioning behavior.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
preview what would be written.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Export dashboards to raw/, prompt/, and provisioning/ files.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard export --profile prod --export-dir ./dashboards --overwrite
.EE
.PP
Export dashboards to raw/, prompt/, and provisioning/ files.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard export --url http://localhost:3000 --token "$GRAFANA_API_TOKEN" --export-dir ./dashboards --overwrite
.EE
.PP
Export dashboards to raw/, prompt/, and provisioning/ files.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard export --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --all-orgs --export-dir ./dashboards --overwrite
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-dashboard\fR(1)
